snippet: Japan's Kei Nishikori notched one of the biggest wins of the year's grand slam with his five-set upset of world number two Andy Murray in the quarter-finals of the U.S. Open but that four-hour victory took its toll on him on Friday....
lead_paragraph: Japan's Kei Nishikori notched one of the biggest wins of the year's grand slam with his five-set upset of world number two Andy Murray in the quarter-finals of the U.S. Open but that four-hour victory took its toll on him on Friday.

headline.print_headline: 'Tired' Nishikori Takes Positives Out of Open Despite Loss
headline.main: 'Tired' Nishikori Takes Positives Out of Open Despite Loss
